Reasoning: The paper discusses the influence of stochastic properties of the string's source and the noise on the channel on the distribution of the number of attempts required to identify the string. This involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) as the paper deals with guessing a password. The use of techniques such as friendly jamming with pseudo-random sequences suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as it discusses filling in the missing pieces of the string.
